reviewText:
Muddy Heights 2 is a ♥♥♥♥♥♥ game, but a funny one. You have to ♥♥♥♥ all things from above and get points for it. Controls are simple but good, same with graphics and sound. There are three levels, each are not very big and last only a few seconds, but you do it over and over again for better points, secrets and money (with that, you can buy boosters before you ♥♥♥♥). All in all it is a cheap, ♥♥♥♥♥♥ games which is fun for a few minutes from time to time. I recommend it.

Don't get me wrong, it's a fun game, but a little to expensive for the play time you get out of it.

Still not a bad game though, just a bit expensive.
